# SporeData RedCAP CAT API

The CAT API uses mirt and mirtCAT for IRT parameter estimation, plumber for simple API development and Redis for in-memory and persistent data storage.



1. Change PROMIS URL in RedCap MySQL:
UPDATE redcap_config SET value = 'http://127.0.0.1:5234/' WHERE field_name = 'promis_api_base_url';
Original API: https://www.redcap-cats.org/promis_api/
Change the user permissions:
GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, ALTER, DROP ON redcap.* TO redcap@'%' IDENTIFIED BY '#####';
This will cease any RedCAP communication to PROMIS.


2. Install Redis in the system (and the package Redux).


3. Load the dictionaries running load_data.R, each dictionary must be configured inside the file.


4. Configure pm2 (or other process manager) to run_api.R